Twelfth Avenue, at the N.E. corner of W. 55th Street, showing the 6 story Rishel Building at that location. Behind same appears the smoke stack of the Dept. of Sanitation. This civic unit in 1937 will have a modern incinerator plant here occupying the entire avenue frontage from 57th to 55th Streets. The photographer is viewing north eastward across Twelfth Avenue from the river side of same.

A negative print accompanies this photostat reproduction.

April 15, 1934.

Twelfth Avenue, south from West 55th Street, showing constructional detail of the widening and improvement of this marginal thoroughfare. The West Side Vehicular Highway is being continued thru this view. At the left appears a portion of the new westerly frontage of Dewitt Clinton Park. Note the retaining wall.

June 19, 1936

H. B. Hoffman, photo
New York Historical Society
